<inglise>Measurement of incremental costs </inglise>
<eesti>Joonise j&auml;rgi saab &uuml;ksiku tegevuse lisanduvad kulud tuletada j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>On the basis of the Figure, the incremental costs of each activity can be determined as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>- Identifitseerida jooksev &uuml;ldkasutatava telefoniv&otilde;rgu (PSTN) v&otilde;i &uuml;ldkasutatava mobiiltelefoniv&otilde;rgu opereerimisega mitteseotud tegevuste kulumaht (1) ja piir &uuml;ldkasutatava telefoniv&otilde;rgu opereerimisega seotud kulumahu ja sellega mitteseotud tegevuse kulude vahel. </eesti>
<inglise>- Identify the volume of current costs of public switched telephone network (PSTN) or the cost of activities not related to the operation of a public mobile telephone network (1) and the margin of costs related to the operation of a public switched telephone network and the costs of not related activities. </inglise>
<eesti>Muutus mitte-PSTN tegevustega seotud lisanduvates kuludes (joonisel a-b) on defineeritud kui PSTN opereerimisega mitteseotud tegevuste lisanduv kulu (incremental cost of non-PSTN activities). </eesti>
<inglise>Change in the incremental costs of related non-PSTN activities (a-b in the Figure) can be defined as the incremental cost of non-PSTN activities. </inglise>
<eesti>- Identifitseerida jooksev &uuml;lekandev&otilde;rgu opereerimisega seotud kulude kogum ja leida kulude maht, mis j&auml;&auml;ks olemata, kui ei eksisteeriks &uuml;lekandev&otilde;rgu opereerimisega seotud tegevusi. </eesti>
<inglise>- Identify the current aggregate cost related to the operation of the transmission (core) network and determine the volume of costs which would not exist if there were no activities related to the operation of a transmission network. </inglise>
<eesti>Erinevus PSTN v&otilde;rgu kulude ja niisuguse v&otilde;rgu kulude vahel, mis on v&auml;hendatud &uuml;lekandev&otilde;rgu opereerimisega seotud tegevuste v&otilde;rra (joonisel c-d), ongi &uuml;lekandev&otilde;rgu opereerimisega seotud tegevuste lisanduvad kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>Difference in the costs of PSTN and such network costs which have been reduced by the activities related to the operation of the transmission network (c-d in the Figure) is the incremental cost of activities related to the operation of the transmission network. </inglise>
<eesti>- Identifitseerida jooksev juurdep&auml;&auml;suv&otilde;rgu hooldamisega seotud tegevuste kulukogum ja leida kulude maht, mis j&auml;&auml;ksid olemata, kui hoolitsetakse vajalikul tasemel k&uuml;ll PSTN v&otilde;rgu eest, aga ei eksisteeriks juurdep&auml;&auml;suv&otilde;rku. </eesti>
<inglise>- Identify the current aggregate cost related to the maintenance of the access network and determine the volume of cost which would not exist if there was necessary maintenance of PSTN but there was no access network. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellisel juhul juurdep&auml;&auml;su v&otilde;imaldamise lisanduvad kulud on vaheks PSTN v&otilde;rgu kulude ja sellise PSTN v&otilde;rgu vahel, mis koosneb ainult &uuml;lekandev&otilde;rgust (joonisel d-e). </eesti>
<inglise>In that case the incremental cost of providing access is the difference of PSTN costs and such PSTN which only consists of the transmission network (d-e in the Figure). </inglise>
<eesti>Individuaalsete tegevuste lisanduvate kulude summa on kogukuludest v&auml;iksem summa v&otilde;rra, mis v&auml;ljendab &uuml;ldkulusid (joonisel f-g). </eesti>
<inglise>The difference between the total incremental cost of individual activities and the total cost is the sum which equals to common fixed cost (f-g in the Figure). </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kus PSTN (Public Switched Telephone Network) on &uuml;ldkasutatav telefoniv&otilde;rk. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Where PSTN is public switched telephone network. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldkasutatava mobiiltelefoniv&otilde;rgu operaatori korral on &uuml;ldkasutatava telefoniv&otilde;rgu (PSTN) asemel antud joonisel &uuml;ldkasutatav mobiiltelefoniv&otilde;rk. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of public mobile telephone network operators, the public mobile telephone network is given in the Figure instead of the public switched telephone network. </inglise>
